Description: Defer the FastMCP import in mcp.server until first attribute access
 `mcp.server.__init__` eagerly imported `from .fastmcp import FastMCP`,
 which in turn pulled `pydantic_settings`, `sse_starlette`, and the
 starlette HTTP transports at module load time. Avalan ships Noble's
 archive plus a thin PPA layer that omits those three packages — they
 are only reachable from FastMCP's HTTP / SSE paths, which Avalan does
 not invoke. Switch to a PEP 562 `__getattr__` shim so the import
 happens lazily on first attribute access. The public surface
 (`from mcp.server import FastMCP`) is preserved; only callers that
 actually touch FastMCP pay the cost of resolving its transitive
 deps. Without this, `import mcp` itself fails on a Noble host
 because of the missing pydantic_settings.
Author: Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-05-19

--- a/src/mcp/server/__init__.py
+++ b/src/mcp/server/__init__.py
@@ -1,5 +1,12 @@
-from .fastmcp import FastMCP
 from .lowlevel import NotificationOptions, Server
 from .models import InitializationOptions

 __all__ = ["Server", "FastMCP", "NotificationOptions", "InitializationOptions"]
+
+
+def __getattr__(name):
+    if name == "FastMCP":
+        from .fastmcp import FastMCP
+
+        return FastMCP
+    raise AttributeError(f"module {__name__!r} has no attribute {name!r}")
